record_data.record_plain_text:
ATTACHMENT A
Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 Radford's Run Wind Farm, LLC Reactive Power Compensation March 29, 2018
RADFORD'S RUN WIND FARM, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Radford's Run Wind Farm, LLC ("Radford's Run") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Radford's Run generating facility ("Radford's Run Facility").
The Radford's Run Facility is a wind turbine generating facility located in Macon County, Illinois. The Radford's Run Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Commonwealth Edison Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Radford's Run's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Radford's Run Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Radford's Run's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Radford's Run shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission, Energy and Operating Reserve Markets Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $700,000.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $58,333.33.
